loans <- read_fst(path="/home/dimuthu/SSRN Oct 2021/Predictability/loans_2.fst",as.data.table = T)
loans[,log_odds:=log(default_probability/(1-default_probability))]
loans[,fico_cat:=ifelse(fico_score>=600 & fico_score<630,"600-629",
                        ifelse(fico_score<660,"630-659",
                               # ifelse(fico_score<660,"640-650",
                                      ifelse(fico_score<700,"660-699",
                                             ifelse(fico_score>=700,"700+",NA))))]

loans[,fico_cat:=ifelse(fico_score>=600 & fico_score<700,floor(fico_score/20)*20,
                        ifelse(fico_score>=700,700,NA))]

loans[,vantage_cat:=ifelse(vantage_score>=600 & fico_score<630,"600-629",
                        ifelse(vantage_score<660,"630-659",
                               # ifelse(fico_score<660,"640-650",
                                      ifelse(vantage_score<700,"660-699",
                                             ifelse(vantage_score>=700,"700+",NA))))]


loans[,pd_bin:=floor(default_probability*100/10)*10]
loans[,pd_bin:=ifelse(pd_bin>=50,50,pd_bin)]
loans[,fico_bin:=floor(fico_score/20)*20]
loans[,huntington_rejected:=ifelse((fico_score>=690 & fico_score<740 & dti<35 & loan_amount<=25000) |
                                   (fico_score>740 & dti<45 & loan_amount<=60000),
                                   "Denied","Approved"
                                  )]


predicted_values <- readRDS("/home/dimuthu/SSRN Oct 2021/CFPB Model/predicted_cfpb_outcomes.rds")

loans <- merge(loans,predicted_values,by="upstart_id")
loans[,counterfactual_bin:=ntile(predicted_def_prob,10)]

Key takeaway: Upstart’s model is different and it identifies the borrowers with different risk levels conditional on output of traditional models (i.e. within each risk level as given by the traditional model). Upstart is able to identify risk that is orthogonal to risk measured by traditional models.

1 Upstart probablity of default density

ggplot(loans[fico_score>=600 & fico_score<760 & loan_year %in% 2020], 
       aes(x = default_probability*100, y = factor(fico_bin))) +
  coord_flip() + 
  xlim(c(0,60))+
  geom_density_ridges(fill = "dodgerblue3",alpha=0.5,color="white",scale=1)+
  theme_minimal()+
  labs(y="Credit score",x="Upstart probability of default (%)")

ggplot(loans[fico_score>=600 & fico_score<760 & loan_year %in% 2020 & !is.na(counterfactual_bin)], 
       aes(x = default_probability*100, y = factor(counterfactual_bin,levels = 10:1))) +
  coord_flip() + 
  xlim(c(0,60))+
  geom_density_ridges(fill = "dodgerblue3",alpha=0.5,color="white",scale=1)+
  theme_minimal()+
  labs(y="Counterfacutal model output decile",x="Upstart probability of default (%)")

ggplot(loans[fico_score>=600 & fico_score<760 & loan_year %in% 2020 & !is.na(counterfactual_bin)], 
       aes(x = default_probability*100, y = factor(huntington_rejected,levels = c("Denied","Approved")))) +
  coord_flip() + 
  xlim(c(0,60))+
  geom_density_ridges(fill = "dodgerblue3",alpha=0.5,color="white",scale=0.75)+
  theme_minimal()+
  labs(y="Large bank underwriting model outcome",x="Upstart probability of default (%)")

controls = "+log(1+annual_income)+dti+borrower_age+I(borrower_age^2)+log(1+number_of_accounts)+log(1+inquiries_past_6_months)+log(1+total_balance)+log(1+credit_history)+log(1+num_accounts_opened_in_past_12_months)+log(1+revolving_pct*100)+log(1+mortgage_pct*100)+log(1+creditcard_utilization*100)+log(1+g051s_percentage_of_trades_ever_delinquent*100)"

covlabs <- c("log(Annual income)","Debt-to-income","Age of the borrower","Age of the borrower2","log(Number of accounts)","log(Number of inquiries)","log(Total liabilities)","log(Credit history)","log(No of recently opened accounts)","log(Pct. of revolving liabilities)","log(Pct. of mortgage liabilities)","log(Credit card utilization)","log(Pct. trades ever delinquent)","log(Loan amount)","Credit score","Counterfactual model output")
delform1 <- paste0("~factor(pd_bin)+",controls,"+log(loan_amount)+fico_score|zip_year+contract_years+ficobin|0|zip_code")
delform2 <- paste0("~factor(pd_bin)+",controls,"+log(loan_amount)+predicted_def_prob|zip_year+contract_years+counterfactual_bin|0|zip_code")
delform3 <- paste0("~factor(pd_bin)+",controls,"+log(loan_amount)|zip_year+contract_years+huntington_rejected|0|zip_code")
chargeform1 <- paste0("~factor(pd_bin)+",controls,"+log(loan_amount)+fico_score|zip_year+contract_years+ficobin|0|zip_code")
chargeform2 <- paste0("~factor(pd_bin)+",controls,"+log(loan_amount)+predicted_def_prob|zip_year+contract_years+counterfactual_bin|0|zip_code")

temp <- loans[fico_score>=600 & fico_score<760 & loan_year %in% 2019:2020,c("chargedoff","delinquent","fico_score","pd_bin")]
temp[,fico_bin:=floor(fico_score/20)*20]

temp_summary <- temp[,.(chargedoff=mean(chargedoff),delinquent=mean(delinquent)),by=.(fico_bin,pd_bin)]

p_tile <- ggplot(temp_summary,aes(x=factor(fico_bin),y=factor(pd_bin),fill=floor(delinquent*100)))+geom_tile()+
  labs(x="Credit score",y="Upstart probability of default (%)",fill="Default rate %")+
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(legend.position = "bottom",legend.title = element_text("Default rate %"),legend.key.size = unit(1, "cm"))+
  scale_fill_gradientn(colors=c("slategray1","skyblue2","dodgerblue3","gray10"))

print(p_tile)

  scale_fill_gradientn(colors=c("slategray1","skyblue2","dodgerblue3","gray10"))

print(p_tile)

temp <- loans[!is.na(huntington_rejected) & fico_score>=600 & fico_score<760 & loan_year %in% 2019:2020,c("chargedoff","delinquent","fico_score","pd_bin","huntington_rejected")]
temp[,fico_bin:=floor(fico_score/20)*20]

temp_summary <- temp[,.(chargedoff=mean(chargedoff),delinquent=mean(delinquent)),by=.(huntington_rejected,pd_bin)]

p_tile <- ggplot(temp_summary,aes(x=factor(huntington_rejected,levels = c("Denied","Approved")),y=factor(pd_bin),fill=floor(delinquent*100)))+geom_tile()+
  labs(x="Large bank underwriting model outcome",y="Upstart probability of default (%)",fill="Default rate %")+
  theme_minimal()+
  theme(legend.position = "bottom",legend.title = element_text("Default rate %"),legend.key.size = unit(1, "cm"))+
  scale_fill_gradientn(colors=c("slategray1","skyblue2","dodgerblue3","gray10"))

print(p_tile)
